The company announced on Friday that it’s rolling out access to DMs on the web to everyone globally.
Instagram has been testing web DMs with a small group of users since January, and the experience isn’t changing with the wider rollout.
DMs on the web will be available to all global usersWeb DMs are especially convenient for people who use Instagram all the time, like reporters, influencers, and social media managers.
Bringing DMs to the web fits with Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg’s broader vision for the company’s future.
He also said he eventually wants to allow Facebook, WhatsApp, and Instagram users to message each other, regardless of the platform they’re using.